<inglise> (1) Following its Decisions of 20 March 1972, 26 June 1976 and 31 December 1981, by Regulations (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 3830/1991(6) and (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 3831/1991(7), the Council inserted Annex XI to the Staff Regulations which confirms and further defines the method for the adjustment of remuneration, and Article 66a which introduces a temporary contribution deducted from the remuneration of officials and other servants of the Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Social partnerships which tend to avoid conflict have thus been a feature of relations between the European institutions and their staff and other servants with regard to the adjustment of remuneration. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) p&auml;rast oma 20. m&auml;rtsi 1972. aasta, 26. juuni 1976. aasta ja 31. detsembri 1981. aasta otsuseid lisas n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rustega (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 3830/1991 (6) ja (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 3831/1991 (7) personalieeskirjadele XI lisa, millega kinnitatakse ja m&auml;&auml;ratletakse t&auml;psemalt t&ouml;&ouml;tasu kohandamise meetod, ja artikli 66a, millega kehtestatakse &uuml;henduste ametnike ja muude teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml;tasust mahaarvatav ajutine maks; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) The current method and the temporary contribution expire on 30 June 2001 whereas the proposal from the Commission to the Council on revisions to the Staff Regulations in connection with the reform is scheduled for December 2001. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) t&ouml;&ouml;tajate ja t&ouml;&ouml;andjate koost&ouml;&ouml;, mille eesm&auml;rk on v&auml;ltida vastuolusid, on seoses t&ouml;&ouml;tasu kohandamisega olnud Euroopa &uuml;henduste institutsioonide ning nende ametnike ja muude teenistujate vaheliste suhete tunnusjooneks; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Extending by two years the period of validity of the "compromise method" would thus avoid having to conduct two separate sets of negotiations between the staff and the institutions, one on the reform and one on remuneration and pensions. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) praegune meetod ja ajutine maks muutuvad kehtetuks 30. juunil 2001, samas kui komisjoni ettepanek n&otilde;ukogule personalieeskirjade l&auml;bivaatamiseks seoses muudatustega on kavandatud 2001. aasta detsembrisse; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) The Staff Regulations of Officials and the Conditions of Employment applicable to Other Servants should therefore be amended to extend the period of validity of the method for adjusting remunerations and the temporary contribution, </inglise>
